2
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:04,120
Hi, I'm Özlem. I'm from Turkey and here is my question

3
00:00:04,760 --> 00:00:06,880
What are some tips in language learning?

4
00:00:08,220 --> 00:00:15,420
I have been an ESL teacher for over 20 years and I would like to say a few things about language learning

5
00:00:16,320 --> 00:00:21,620
I always see people trying to find a shortcut in language learning

6
00:00:22,620 --> 00:00:30,100
Yes, you can have a shortcut in the sense of time, but I don't believe you can have a shortcut in the sense of effort

7
00:00:30,800 --> 00:00:36,980
So, number one, you should find the reason why do you want to learn this language

8
00:00:37,740 --> 00:00:44,240
For example, if you want to speak fluently, you should focus on speaking and listening activities

9
00:00:44,240 --> 00:00:52,620
I generally see people complaining about the amount of time they have spent and have no result at the end

10
00:00:53,300 --> 00:01:02,280
But when we look closer at their studies, we see that they have not spent enough time in that specific skill they want

11
00:01:03,640 --> 00:01:06,780
And secondly, you should follow a system

12
00:01:07,940 --> 00:01:18,520
If you follow a system, if you have a system, and thirdly, if you have fun, this is very important, you will definitely learn the language

13
00:01:19,360 --> 00:01:26,600
So, have a system and have fun. Love what you are doing. Thank you. See you later. Bye
